            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><addressee>Mr. Joseph M. Asch</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#47; </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">When I came back to town last evening I understood that you should
                have&#47; said&#44; that I had written a letter to <placeName>New York</placeName>
                cautioning the people there against&#47; giving any thing to the congr. of seceders
                of whom I have reason to believe that&#47; you are one. Now&#44; as I have not seen
                you to speak with you for several weeks past&#44;&#47; it is impossible for you to
                know any thing about my movements from your own&#47; knowledge&#44; even if I had
                written such a letter&#44; which permit me to say I would&#47; have been as much
                authorized to do&#44; as for you to go on to <placeName>New York</placeName> to beg
                for&#47; a congr. which as yet exists only in imagination. But as I have written no
                letters to&#47; <placeName>N. Y</placeName><hi rend="sup">o</hi>. except to <persName>Mr.
                    Lyons</persName> the Haz. of the <add>&#63;</add> cong. in answer to a
                friendly one&#47; from him&#44; and one to <persName> Mr. Kursheedt</persName> on
                business relating to <persName>Mr. Nelson</persName>&#44; I demand&#47; of you the
                name of the person who invented the falsehood and told it to you. For my&#47;
                private letters I am not responsible to you&#44; or any one&#44; and I cannot
                permit&#47; my name to be used any longer to answer the purposes of the seceders. I
                would&#47; not have noticed the falsehood if it were the only one of its kind&#59;
                but as I have&#47; been so often spoken of without cause I must insist upon your
                disclosing the&#47; name of your informant to the bearer of this&#44;<persName>Mr.
                     Sl. N. Carvalho</persName>.&#47; <placeName>Phila</placeName><hi
                    rend="sup">a</hi>. Friday <date>July 10</date><hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44;
                    <date>Tamuz 9</date><hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                <date>5600</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>.&#47; </p>
        </body>
